quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  40,69,Seest thou not those who cavil at the signs of God? how are they turned aside
  40,70,"They who treat \"the Book,\" and the message with which we have sent our Sent Ones, as a lie, shall know the truth hereafter"
  40,71,When the collars shall be on their necks and the chains to drag them
  40,72,"into Hell: then in the fire shall they be burned"
  40,73,"Then shall it be said to them, \"Where are they whom ye made the objects of joint worship with God"
  40,74,"They shall say, \"They have vanished away from us. Yea, it was nought on which we called heretofore.\" Thus God leadeth the unbelievers astray"
  40,75,"This for you, because of your unrighteous insolence and immoderate joys on earth"
  40,76,"Enter ye the portals of Hell to abide therein for ever. And, wretched the abode of the haughty ones"
  40,77,"Therefore be thou steadfast in patience: for the promise of God is truth: and whether we shall make thee see part of the woes with which we threatened them, or whether we cause thee first to die, unto us shall they be brought back"
  40,78,"And we have already sent apostles before thee: of some we have told thee, and of others we have told thee nothing: but no apostle had the power to work a miracle unless by the leave of God. But when God's behest cometh, everything will be decided with truth: and then they perish who treated it as a vain thing"